      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "# Latest AI News Today\n\nHere's a roundup of the top AI stories making headlines:\n\n## Major Industry Moves\n\n- **Google's massive Anthropic investment**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Google is committing US$40 billion to its AI rival Anthropic, as the firm looks to secure cloud dominance and fuel the expansion of Gen AI infrastructure."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n- **Alphabet's cloud surge**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The AI infrastructure arms race hit full throttle as Alphabet broke away with a 63% surge in Google Cloud revenue to US$20 billion for Q1 2026."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n- **Apple leadership change**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Tim Cook is stepping down as CEO after serving Apple for 15 years, leaving John Ternus as his successor."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n- **Meta expands into robotics**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Meta has acquired a robotics AI company to help build humanoid technology."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## High-Profile Legal Battle\n\n- **Musk vs. Altman trial**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The civil trial between the tech billionaires kicked off Monday and could help define the future of artificial intelligence. The trial is scheduled to run for four weeks, with a cast of prominent tech executives set to take the stand."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Musk claimed Altman betrayed the original principles of OpenAI to remain a nonprofit and that the company benefited from his money and connections."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## AI in Government & Defense\n\n- **Pentagon partnerships**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Google has joined OpenAI in allowing the Pentagon to use its AI systems, while rival Anthropic remains embroiled in a court battle after seeking stronger safeguards."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Markets & Infrastructure\n\n- **Cerebras IPO**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "AI chipmaker Cerebras is reportedly targeting up to $4 billion in its IPO."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n- **Apple Mac Mini price hike**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Apple raised the Mac Mini's starting price to $799 after AI frenzy drained supply."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n- **Security concerns**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "An AI company's own experts warned that Mythos could hack the systems beneath most modern computing, and banks and government agencies are racing to gauge the threat."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Regulation & Policy\n\n- **Florida data center bill**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Governor DeSantis is emerging as a voice of AI skepticism in the Republican Party, but state lawmakers declined to take up his push for legislation."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The bill had passed both chambers of the state Legislature and would have imposed the country's first statewide moratorium on new data center construction."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Enterprise AI & Hiring\n\n- **Amazon's AI recruiter**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
